⊕meta⊕
name = "sky-library-health-report"
description = "Compose per-workflow lint status, run-recency, and budget-cap presence into a one-screen graded HEALTH.md (red/amber/green) for a whole .sky library."
params.dir.type = "string"
params.dir.required = true
params.dir.description = "Directory containing the .sky files to grade."
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
max_budget_usd = 0.5
ui = "ui/workflow"
⊕⊕

※inventory※
Enumerate .sky files in SKY_DIR; fail if dir missing or empty. No dependencies.
※※

§inventory§
bash_file = "./scripts/inventory.sh"
ui = "ui/inventory"
§§

※checks※
Per-file lint pass/fail, uncapped-LLM detection, last-run recency; emit TSV. Depends_on: inventory, trigger_rule: all_success.
※※

§checks§
depends_on = ["inventory"]
trigger_rule = "all_success"
bash_file = "./scripts/checks.sh"
ui = "ui/checks"
§§

※render※
Grade each workflow row (red/amber/green by lint/cap/recency); write HEALTH.md. Depends_on: checks, trigger_rule: all_success, model: haiku.
※※

§render§
model = "haiku"
depends_on = ["checks"]
trigger_rule = "all_success"
ui = "ui/render"
§§

∆render∆
You are writing a one-screen library health dashboard. Read the tab-separated rows in environment variable SKY_OUTPUT_CHECKS. The header row is: workflow, lint, llm_uncapped, last_run.

Write a Markdown file to the path in environment variable SKY_DIR, named HEALTH.md (i.e. {{dir}}/HEALTH.md). Use the Write tool. Overwrite if it exists.

Grade each workflow row red/amber/green by these exact rules, in priority order:
- RED if lint == fail.
- AMBER if lint == pass AND (llm_uncapped == yes OR last_run == never).
- GREEN if lint == pass AND llm_uncapped == no AND last_run != never.

File contents, in this order:
1. An H1 title: "# .sky Library Health".
2. A one-line rollup sentence: total workflows and a count per grade, e.g. "12 workflows: 8 green, 3 amber, 1 red."
3. A Markdown table with columns: Workflow | Grade | Lint | LLM cap | Last run. Render Grade as a colored circle emoji plus the word (red circle RED, amber/yellow circle AMBER, green circle GREEN). For LLM cap: "uncapped" when llm_uncapped == yes, "ok" otherwise. For Last run: "never" or "seen".
4. A short "What this means" section (3-4 bullets): red = lint failing, fix first; amber = passes lint but is an uncapped LLM workflow or has never run; green = clean and exercised. State plainly that this report COMPOSES the lint, budget-cap, and run-recency signals into a dashboard and is NOT a substitute for the dedicated audits — run audit-sky-library, dry-run-sky-workflow, and the budget audit for per-issue detail.

Keep it under one screen. Terse. No preamble in your chat reply; just write the file and report the path and the grade tallies.
∆∆

※verify※
Assert HEALTH.md exists and is non-empty. Depends_on: render, trigger_rule: all_success.
※※

§verify§
depends_on = ["render"]
trigger_rule = "all_success"
bash_file = "./scripts/verify.sh"
ui = "ui/verify"
§§

※※
sky-library-health-report
==========================

One-screen graded HEALTH.md for a whole .sky library. Composes three cheap
signals per workflow into a red/amber/green dashboard:

  - lint pass/fail        (red when failing)
  - LLM budget cap        (amber when a claude node has no max_budget_usd)
  - run recency           (amber when the workflow has never run)
  - green                 (lint passes, capped-or-no-LLM, and seen in run history)

HONESTY: this is a DASHBOARD that rolls up existing signals. It does not
re-audit deeply. For per-issue detail run the dedicated workflows:
  - audit-sky-library        (full library scan + report)
  - dry-run-sky-workflow     (probe a single workflow)
  - the budget audit         (token/cost detail)

DAG
---
  inventory ──► checks ──► render ──► verify
   (bash)       (bash)     (haiku)     (bash)

  inventory   list "$SKY_DIR"/*.sky; fail if dir missing or empty.
  checks      per file: skyway lint pass/fail, claude-node-without-cap detection,
              best-effort last-run recency from `skyway logs`; emit TSV rows.
  render      haiku reads $SKY_OUTPUT_CHECKS, grades each row, writes
              "$SKY_DIR"/HEALTH.md (table + one-line rollup).
  verify      assert HEALTH.md exists and is non-empty.

RUN
---
  skyway run sky-library-health-report --vars dir=/path/to/.sky/workflows

VARS
----
  dir   (required)  Directory containing the *.sky files to grade.
                    Exposed to bash as "$SKY_DIR" and to the prompt as {{dir}}.
                    HEALTH.md is written into this same directory.

NOTES
-----
  - No `rm -f`/`rm -r`: nothing is deleted; render overwrites HEALTH.md in place.
  - last_run is best-effort (greps `skyway logs` for the workflow basename); a
    "never" can be a false negative if logs were pruned — treat amber as a nudge.
  - max_budget_usd caps the single haiku render node.
※※
